# MovieHive (React + Vite)

MovieHive is a modern React application for discovering movies using the OMDb API. It features Google OAuth login, a clean Tailwind UI, fast client-side routing, and a simple global store for fetching/searching movies.

## Features

- Authentication: Google OAuth via `@react-oauth/google` and a mock email/password flow
- Search & Details: Query OMDb, view results and navigate to a movie details page
- Routing & Navigation: Sidebar with active state using `react-router-dom`
- State Management: Lightweight global store powered by `zustand`
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + responsive layout
- Tooling: Vite for fast dev builds and previews

## Tech Stack

- React 19, Vite 5
- React Router DOM 7
- Zustand 5
- Axios for API calls
- Tailwind CSS 3
- React Icons

## Project Structure

```
App/
	movie-app/
		src/
			App.jsx
			main.jsx
			index.css
			Oauth/
				LoginPage.jsx
				SignupPage.jsx
			pages/
				Home.jsx
				MovieDetails.jsx
				Movies.jsx
				TvSeries.jsx
				Upcoming.jsx
			components/
				SearchBar.jsx
				MovieCard.jsx
			store/
				useMovieStore.js
			service/
				api.js
		vite.config.js
		package.json
		.env (not committed)
```

- App entry: see [src/main.jsx](src/main.jsx)
- Routing: see [src/App.jsx](src/App.jsx)
- Auth screens: [src/Oauth/LoginPage.jsx](src/Oauth/LoginPage.jsx), [src/Oauth/SignupPage.jsx](src/Oauth/SignupPage.jsx)
- State & API: [src/store/useMovieStore.js](src/store/useMovieStore.js) and [src/service/api.js](src/service/api.js)

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ and npm
- OMDb API key: https://www.omdbapi.com/apikey.aspx
- Google OAuth Client ID (OAuth 2.0, Web application)

## Setup

1) Clone or open the project and move into the app folder:

```powershell
cd "App/movie-app"
```

2) Create an `.env` file with your OMDb key:

```dotenv
VITE_OMDB_API_KEY=your_omdb_key
```

3) Configure Google OAuth:

- Open [src/main.jsx](src/main.jsx) and set your Client ID in `GoogleOAuthProvider`.
- Optional: you can move this to an env var (e.g., `VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`) and read with `import.meta.env.VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`.

4) Install dependencies and start the dev server:

```powershell
npm install
npm run dev
```

Visit http://localhost:5173/ and log in. After successful auth you’ll be redirected to `/home`.

## Scripts

- `dev`: Start Vite dev server
- `build`: Build for production
- `preview`: Preview the production build locally
- `lint`: Run ESLint

## Routing

- `/login` – Login page (Google OAuth + email/password)
- `/signup` – Signup page
- `/home` – Main dashboard with search and trending grid
- `/movies` – Movies placeholder page
- `/series` – TV series placeholder page
- `/upcoming` – Upcoming content placeholder page
- `/movie/:id` – Movie details page

## Environment Variables

- `VITE_OMDB_API_KEY` – OMDb API key used in [src/service/api.js](src/service/api.js)
- (Optional) `VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` – If you externalize the Google Client ID

> Never commit your `.env` file. Store secrets securely.

## Implementation Notes

- `useMovieStore` exposes `searchMovies(query)` and `getMovieDetails(id)` and keeps `movies`, `selectedMovie`, `loading`, `error`.
- `SearchBar` calls `searchMovies(query)` on submit.
- `MovieCard` links to the details route using the `imdbID`.
- Sidebar uses `NavLink` for active styles and navigation.
- Logout simply navigates back to `/login`.

## Troubleshooting

- Blank/404 at `localhost:5173/`: ensure `npm run dev` is running and the terminal hasn’t been closed.
- "vite is not recognized": run `npm install` in the `App/movie-app` folder to install local binaries.
- Google login keeps authenticating: verify your OAuth Client ID, allowed origin (`http://localhost:5173`), and that the dev server remains running.
- No search results: check your OMDb key and network access; the API quota may apply.

